            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On August 2, 1949, Ambassador Grady appeared before the Committee on Foreign
                    Affairs of the House of Representatives to testify in favor of the passage of
                    the Mutual Defense Assistance Act of 1949. In his prepared statement and his
                    subsequent testimony, Ambassador Grady reviewed United States military
                    assistance to Greece and the course of the efforts of the Greek Government to
                    suppress the Greek guerrilla movement. For the text of his statement and
                    testimony, see <hi rend="italic">Mutual Defense Assistance Act of 1949:</hi>
                    Hearings before the House Committee on Foreign Affairs, 81st Cong., 1st sess.,
                    on H.R. 5748 and H.R. 5895 (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1949), pages
                    131–160.</p>
            </div>
